examples.en: The police controlled the crowd.
Access to the site is closely controlled.
Political activity is closely controlled.
He controlled the urge to laugh.
Newman controlled himself with an effort.
The guerrillas controlled half the country.
The test was done under controlled conditions.
They controlled the greater part of North Africa.
The lights on stage are controlled by this computer.
He controlled a cattle empire in the heart of Texas.
He controlled the volume by turning the radio's knob.
The building had only electronically controlled doors.
These animals were raised in a controlled environment.
Police carried out a controlled explosion of the device.
The country's elite owned or controlled most of the wealth.
Under these conditions, the fire can be rapidly controlled.
The polar bears at the zoo live in a controlled environment.
The population of rabbits is controlled by natural predators.
In most instances the disease can be controlled by medication.
Game preserves allow only carefully controlled hunting and fishing.
The superabundance of life is controlled by the law of mutual destruction.
Development in areas of outstanding natural beauty is strictly controlled.
